1
00:00:14,633 --> 00:00:18,900
Now you're saying you love
the son of that witch

2
00:00:18,967 --> 00:00:22,467
who made my life miserable!

3
00:00:22,533 --> 00:00:25,833
I will be in pain forever!

4
00:00:25,900 --> 00:00:27,000
Mom, I love Yenyen.

5
00:00:27,067 --> 00:00:28,467
What I feel for her is real.

6
00:00:28,533 --> 00:00:30,400
Sorry, but I can't obey you
this time.

7
00:00:30,467 --> 00:00:31,900
Red! Red!

8
00:00:32,933 --> 00:00:34,833
Rina won't leave you alone!

9
00:00:34,933 --> 00:00:37,233
She will take it out on you.

10
00:00:37,300 --> 00:00:41,867
She will forever make you pay
for something that I didn't do!

11
00:00:41,933 --> 00:00:43,667
She's not the one
who killed him.

12
00:00:43,733 --> 00:00:46,233
She's still the reason
Angelo died.

13
00:00:46,300 --> 00:00:49,333
Yenyen has nothing to do
with her mother's crime.

14
00:00:49,400 --> 00:00:50,633
But still!

15
00:00:50,700 --> 00:00:54,700
If you love Eden, you'll have
to love her family too.

16
00:00:54,767 --> 00:00:56,667
And how can you love Amanda?

17
00:00:56,733 --> 00:00:58,700
I'm perfectly fine.

18
00:00:58,767 --> 00:01:01,000
- Really?
- It was just an act.

19
00:01:01,067 --> 00:01:02,233
I convinced him, right?

20
00:01:02,300 --> 00:01:03,267
See, he didn't leave.

21
00:01:03,333 --> 00:01:05,400
So you were faking?

22
00:01:05,467 --> 00:01:07,167
You weren't sick.

23
00:01:07,267 --> 00:01:08,367
You lied to me.

24
00:01:09,467 --> 00:01:12,100
Mom, I love you so much.

25
00:01:12,167 --> 00:01:15,533
I'll be sad without you.

26
00:01:15,600 --> 00:01:17,233
Mom, I need you.

27
00:01:33,533 --> 00:01:34,500
Yen!

28
00:01:37,567 --> 00:01:40,500
- Yen.
- Red, why are you here?

29
00:01:40,600 --> 00:01:42,033
You didn't pick up your phone.

30
00:01:42,100 --> 00:01:43,500
I was worried about you.

31
00:01:43,567 --> 00:01:45,400
You should go.
My mom might wake up.

32
00:01:45,467 --> 00:01:47,100
She'll be furious.

33
00:01:47,167 --> 00:01:49,467
Yen, I'm not leaving, okay?

34
00:01:49,533 --> 00:01:50,900
I'll talk to her.

35
00:01:50,967 --> 00:01:53,300
I'll tell her
that we love each other.

36
00:01:53,367 --> 00:01:55,533
And we shouldn't get involved
with their problem.

37
00:01:57,167 --> 00:01:58,167
You can't do that.

38
00:01:58,233 --> 00:02:00,200
They'll get hurt.

39
00:02:00,267 --> 00:02:01,533
I love my mom.

40
00:02:02,700 --> 00:02:04,100
Don't you love me?

41
00:02:05,267 --> 00:02:06,967
Just leave, please.

42
00:02:08,067 --> 00:02:09,233
I'm not going anywhere.

43
00:02:11,867 --> 00:02:14,300
What is he doing here?

44
00:02:15,500 --> 00:02:17,567
Mom, he's leaving.

45
00:02:17,633 --> 00:02:20,500
You have the nerve to come here!

46
00:02:20,567 --> 00:02:22,133
What do you want?

47
00:02:22,200 --> 00:02:24,833
You want to poison
my daughter's head

48
00:02:24,900 --> 00:02:28,200
to carry on this relationship?

49
00:02:28,267 --> 00:02:29,600
No, Ma'am.

50
00:02:29,667 --> 00:02:31,200
I came here to explain.

51
00:02:31,267 --> 00:02:33,400
I don't need your explanation.

52
00:02:33,467 --> 00:02:35,267
Just leave.

53
00:02:35,333 --> 00:02:36,533
Mom, please stop.

54
00:02:36,600 --> 00:02:40,467
I'm not going anywhere
until you hear my side.

55
00:02:40,533 --> 00:02:41,933
Please hear us out.

56
00:02:44,400 --> 00:02:46,233
I love your daughter so much.

57
00:02:46,300 --> 00:02:49,500
And I can forget
everything that happened.

58
00:02:49,600 --> 00:02:50,567
Oh, wow!

59
00:02:50,633 --> 00:02:51,833
Let go of my daughter.

60
00:02:51,900 --> 00:02:52,933
Go inside the house!

61
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:55,800
If you can forget everything,
well, I can't!

62
00:02:55,867 --> 00:02:57,033
You should leave.

63
00:02:58,767 --> 00:03:03,400
Hey! Go on while I can
still hold my temper!

64
00:03:03,467 --> 00:03:06,167
I won't leave
even if you get mad.

65
00:03:06,233 --> 00:03:08,533
Really? Are you that brave?

66
00:03:08,600 --> 00:03:09,567
Are you a tough guy?

67
00:03:16,467 --> 00:03:17,600
How about this?

68
00:03:18,667 --> 00:03:20,367
Do you want this?
Are you leaving or not?

69
00:03:22,367 --> 00:03:23,700
Are you leaving or not?

70
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:41,533
I'm leaving because I don't want
any trouble.

71
00:03:41,600 --> 00:03:43,100
Not because I'm scared.

72
00:03:44,633 --> 00:03:46,500
And I know you're not capable
of hurting anyone.

73
00:03:48,100 --> 00:03:50,533
Yenyen told me
that you're a good person.

74
00:03:51,733 --> 00:03:55,200
I don't believe
that you killed my brother.

75
00:03:55,300 --> 00:03:57,233
Don't try to fool me.

76
00:03:57,300 --> 00:03:59,833
You're just like your mom.

77
00:03:59,900 --> 00:04:01,600
You all think
that I'm a criminal.

78
00:04:01,667 --> 00:04:03,367
A murderer!

79
00:04:03,433 --> 00:04:04,800
I don't believe that.

80
00:04:04,867 --> 00:04:06,933
I don't believe
you're capable of doing that.

81
00:04:08,867 --> 00:04:09,867
Get out of here.

82
00:04:11,667 --> 00:04:13,267
Go!

83
00:04:13,333 --> 00:04:14,467
Leave!

84
00:04:25,167 --> 00:04:26,567
Eden, can you stay still?

85
00:04:26,633 --> 00:04:29,333
I'm getting crossed-eyed
while looking at you.

86
00:04:30,567 --> 00:04:33,733
I'm worried about mom and Red.

87
00:04:33,800 --> 00:04:36,000
I don't know
what's going on downstairs.

88
00:04:37,733 --> 00:04:40,867
I can't ask your mom
to come inside.

89
00:04:41,900 --> 00:04:43,733
I don't think I have the right
to get involved.

90
00:04:44,833 --> 00:04:46,733
I did her wrong.

91
00:04:46,800 --> 00:04:49,000
So now she's mad at us.

92
00:04:50,133 --> 00:04:53,267
I'm sorry, Auntie,
for dragging you into this mess.

93
00:04:53,333 --> 00:04:56,767
I shouldn't have told you
about my relationship with Red.

94
00:04:56,833 --> 00:04:57,900
What are you talking about?

95
00:04:59,767 --> 00:05:01,000
Hello!

96
00:05:01,100 --> 00:05:02,267
I'm your Aunt.

97
00:05:02,333 --> 00:05:04,700
You shouldn't keep secrets
from me.

98
00:05:04,767 --> 00:05:08,867
I was touched
when you told me your secret.

99
00:05:08,933 --> 00:05:11,300
That's probably why your mom
got mad at me.

100
00:05:11,367 --> 00:05:15,800
Because you told me your secret
and you kept it from her.

101
00:05:15,867 --> 00:05:17,967
That's why she's giving us
the cold treatment.

102
00:05:19,500 --> 00:05:20,433
But still...

103
00:05:20,500 --> 00:05:23,267
I shouldn't have gotten you
involved.

104
00:05:25,500 --> 00:05:28,033
Don't worry about it, Eden.

105
00:05:28,100 --> 00:05:30,600
No matter what you go through
in life,

106
00:05:30,667 --> 00:05:32,633
your mom and I
are always here for you.

107
00:05:33,700 --> 00:05:36,800
And don't get upset with her,
okay?

108
00:05:36,900 --> 00:05:38,867
It's only natural for her
to feel like that.

109
00:05:38,933 --> 00:05:41,900
She was hurt.

110
00:05:41,967 --> 00:05:44,700
But I know she will forgive you.

111
00:05:44,767 --> 00:05:45,833
Okay?

112
00:05:48,067 --> 00:05:49,333
I hope so.

113
00:06:00,967 --> 00:06:02,067
How's Red?

114
00:06:02,133 --> 00:06:03,267
Did he respond to your messages?

115
00:06:04,333 --> 00:06:06,067
I'm calling him.
He's not answering his phone.

116
00:06:07,300 --> 00:06:09,233
I'm sure he's with Eden
right now.

117
00:06:09,300 --> 00:06:10,700
Don't try to control him
too much.

118
00:06:10,767 --> 00:06:12,500
He might rebel against us.

119
00:06:12,567 --> 00:06:14,367
You know how kids are nowadays.

120
00:06:14,433 --> 00:06:17,333
They'll want to get away
if you try to control them.

121
00:06:17,400 --> 00:06:19,667
Okay, I'll keep that in mind.

122
00:06:19,733 --> 00:06:21,200
You should go.

123
00:06:21,267 --> 00:06:23,000
You might get late
for your meeting.

124
00:06:33,000 --> 00:06:34,133
Yes, Dear?

125
00:06:34,200 --> 00:06:37,400
Auntie, I think you really need
to know about something.

126
00:06:37,467 --> 00:06:39,533
Know about what?

127
00:06:39,600 --> 00:06:40,933
It's about Red.

128
00:06:41,000 --> 00:06:42,233
He went to see Eden.

129
00:06:43,467 --> 00:06:44,667
How did you know that?

130
00:06:49,100 --> 00:06:50,100
Get out of here!

131
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:13,833
I saw everything, Auntie.

132
00:07:13,900 --> 00:07:16,333
And I saw what Eden's mom
did to him.

133
00:07:27,167 --> 00:07:28,167
Mom...

134
00:07:29,133 --> 00:07:30,700
I love him.

135
00:07:31,833 --> 00:07:34,367
We love each other, Mom.

136
00:07:34,433 --> 00:07:35,800
No.

137
00:07:35,867 --> 00:07:38,000
That's not true.

138
00:07:38,067 --> 00:07:39,733
Take back what you said.

139
00:07:39,800 --> 00:07:41,433
Take it back.

140
00:07:41,500 --> 00:07:42,667
Take it back.

141
00:07:42,733 --> 00:07:44,333
It's not true.

142
00:07:44,400 --> 00:07:45,867
Mom, I'm sorry.

143
00:07:47,967 --> 00:07:49,400
Sorry, Mom.

144
00:07:52,200 --> 00:07:55,267
Mom, how are you feeling?

145
00:07:55,333 --> 00:07:56,800
I made you some coffee.

146
00:07:56,867 --> 00:07:58,967
To ease your drunkenness.

147
00:08:09,367 --> 00:08:11,367
I'm sorry, Mom.

148
00:08:11,433 --> 00:08:14,367
I didn't expect Red
to come here.

149
00:08:14,433 --> 00:08:16,200
Don't worry, I'll talk to him.

150
00:08:16,267 --> 00:08:17,867
He'll listen to me.

151
00:08:17,933 --> 00:08:18,967
Red is kind.

152
00:08:20,633 --> 00:08:23,900
If he's really kind,
he'll stay away from you.

153
00:08:25,067 --> 00:08:26,600
He'll listen to his parents.

154
00:08:26,667 --> 00:08:27,800
He won't disobey them.

155
00:08:30,067 --> 00:08:33,767
Red loves his parents so much.

156
00:08:35,133 --> 00:08:37,000
When we were on the island,

157
00:08:37,067 --> 00:08:40,067
we often talked
about our parents,

158
00:08:40,133 --> 00:08:42,767
especially when we were sad...

159
00:08:42,833 --> 00:08:44,700
when we were losing hope.

160
00:08:46,333 --> 00:08:48,333
That's why I fell for him.

161
00:08:48,400 --> 00:08:52,833
Because we both love
our parents.

162
00:08:58,700 --> 00:09:04,433
And when I told him
that you were in jail,

163
00:09:06,033 --> 00:09:07,533
he didn't judge me.

164
00:09:09,633 --> 00:09:13,367
Who would have thought
that his parents were the ones

165
00:09:13,433 --> 00:09:14,933
who put you in jail?

166
00:09:16,433 --> 00:09:18,933
I'm having a hard time too.

167
00:09:20,467 --> 00:09:22,267
I don't know what to do.

168
00:09:23,467 --> 00:09:25,133
I'm so confused.

169
00:09:27,667 --> 00:09:28,633
Mom...

170
00:09:30,167 --> 00:09:32,167
I didn't betray you.

171
00:09:33,800 --> 00:09:35,567
I just fell in love.

172
00:09:39,300 --> 00:09:41,133
Who do you love more?

173
00:09:42,200 --> 00:09:43,800
Is it me or Red?

174
00:09:47,833 --> 00:09:50,933
Mom, I can love both of you.

175
00:09:51,000 --> 00:09:52,000
No.

176
00:09:53,133 --> 00:09:54,933
You can only choose one.

177
00:10:00,700 --> 00:10:01,867
What?

178
00:10:01,967 --> 00:10:04,633
Your mom is making you choose?

179
00:10:04,700 --> 00:10:07,333
Yes, I don't know what to do
anymore.

180
00:10:08,667 --> 00:10:12,233
Eden, I saw
how much you love Red.

181
00:10:12,300 --> 00:10:16,433
You even had to fight Sabina
for him.

182
00:10:16,500 --> 00:10:18,667
Are you going to give up now?

183
00:10:18,733 --> 00:10:20,667
And you love each other.

184
00:10:22,633 --> 00:10:24,200
I know.

185
00:10:24,267 --> 00:10:25,767
But what am I going to do
with my mom?

186
00:10:27,500 --> 00:10:29,233
You can only choose one.

187
00:10:33,800 --> 00:10:35,233
If you choose him,

188
00:10:37,500 --> 00:10:38,633
I will accept it.

189
00:10:41,267 --> 00:10:42,733
Even if it kills me.

190
00:11:01,233 --> 00:11:04,000
She told me she was hurting.

191
00:11:04,067 --> 00:11:05,633
I can't blame her for it.

192
00:11:05,700 --> 00:11:09,267
Red's family
made our life miserable.

193
00:11:09,367 --> 00:11:11,667
There you go again!

194
00:11:11,733 --> 00:11:12,800
It's his family.

195
00:11:12,867 --> 00:11:14,500
Not him.

196
00:11:14,567 --> 00:11:20,933
And it's a once-in-a-lifetime
chance to find the one.

197
00:11:22,767 --> 00:11:24,167
I know.

198
00:11:24,233 --> 00:11:25,767
But there's a problem.

199
00:11:26,967 --> 00:11:29,667
Our parents are against
our relationship.

200
00:11:31,200 --> 00:11:32,867
Eden...

201
00:11:32,933 --> 00:11:36,467
Why don't you try to fight
for what you want this time?

202
00:11:36,533 --> 00:11:37,700
They can't do anything about it
anyway.

203
00:11:37,767 --> 00:11:41,167
Fight now, come what may later.

204
00:11:41,267 --> 00:11:42,300
Something like that.

205
00:11:49,700 --> 00:11:51,233
Miss Emma, where's my mom?

206
00:11:51,300 --> 00:11:54,033
She left with your Uncle Zandro.

207
00:11:54,100 --> 00:11:55,967
Did she say where she's going?

208
00:11:56,033 --> 00:11:59,367
I heard her talking to Sabina
on the phone earlier.

209
00:11:59,433 --> 00:12:02,400
She's going to...

210
00:12:02,467 --> 00:12:05,433
Eden's house.
I think that's what she said.

211
00:12:09,967 --> 00:12:11,367
And then she left.

212
00:12:16,067 --> 00:12:17,233
Hey!

213
00:12:17,300 --> 00:12:18,767
Who is that?

214
00:12:18,833 --> 00:12:20,500
Who's throwing rocks
at our house?

215
00:12:22,467 --> 00:12:23,433
Who...

216
00:12:26,567 --> 00:12:27,833
You again?

217
00:12:27,900 --> 00:12:29,567
You and your brother!

218
00:12:30,800 --> 00:12:32,100
What do you want?

219
00:12:32,167 --> 00:12:35,067
Do you think I don't know
what you did?

220
00:12:35,133 --> 00:12:36,133
What?

221
00:12:36,200 --> 00:12:38,633
You threaten to kill my son.

222
00:12:38,700 --> 00:12:40,867
What a drama queen.

223
00:12:40,933 --> 00:12:41,967
Threaten to kill him?

224
00:12:43,000 --> 00:12:44,600
I just scared him off

225
00:12:44,667 --> 00:12:47,200
so he'd stop
bothering my daughter!

226
00:12:47,267 --> 00:12:49,667
You still threaten him.

227
00:12:49,767 --> 00:12:52,567
Perhaps you want me
to make a threat.

228
00:12:52,633 --> 00:12:53,600
Oh, aren't you doing it already?

229
00:12:53,667 --> 00:12:55,033
What do you think you're doing?

230
00:12:55,100 --> 00:12:57,100
You're throwing rocks
at our house.

231
00:12:57,167 --> 00:12:58,433
That's nothing, Amanda.

232
00:12:59,433 --> 00:13:01,267
- Zandro...
- Yes?

233
00:13:01,333 --> 00:13:04,133
Show her what you're about
to throw at her house.

234
00:13:13,167 --> 00:13:14,500
Did you like my bomb threat?

235
00:13:15,867 --> 00:13:17,600
Both of you have the nerve
to do this.

236
00:13:17,667 --> 00:13:19,567
You're going to involve
innocent people?

237
00:13:20,700 --> 00:13:23,033
Why don't you get yourself
blown up too?

238
00:13:23,133 --> 00:13:26,633
No. It's all your fault, Amanda.

239
00:13:26,700 --> 00:13:28,533
I wouldn't be here

240
00:13:28,600 --> 00:13:30,600
if you didn't do anything
to my son.

241
00:13:30,667 --> 00:13:33,300
You know that I hate losing.

242
00:13:34,300 --> 00:13:36,767
You killed my firstborn already,

243
00:13:36,833 --> 00:13:38,233
and now you want to do it
to my other son too.

244
00:13:38,300 --> 00:13:39,733
- I won't let you do that.
- You're annoying.

245
00:13:39,800 --> 00:13:41,200
I'll kill you first.

246
00:13:43,233 --> 00:13:44,233
Mom!

247
00:13:45,300 --> 00:13:46,967
So she's here to the rescue
again.

248
00:13:47,033 --> 00:13:48,333
What's going on here?

249
00:13:48,400 --> 00:13:50,300
These two had lost their minds!

250
00:13:50,367 --> 00:13:51,233
- What's that?
- Look at them.
Why is he holding a grenade?

251
00:13:52,300 --> 00:13:53,967
- What is that for?
- I will shove it

252
00:13:54,033 --> 00:13:55,567
in your sister's mouth!

253
00:13:55,667 --> 00:13:57,033
Ma'am Rina, please stop.

254
00:13:57,100 --> 00:13:58,800
You'll get other people hurt!

255
00:13:59,833 --> 00:14:02,100
Are you going to kill
the whole village?

256
00:14:04,533 --> 00:14:06,733
Why don't you just swallow
that thing?

257
00:14:06,800 --> 00:14:08,133
It will fit your mouth better.

258
00:14:08,200 --> 00:14:11,733
- Oh, really?
- Yes.

259
00:14:11,800 --> 00:14:12,733
Mom!

260
00:14:14,400 --> 00:14:16,600
- Uncle Zandro.
- Red, please.

261
00:14:16,667 --> 00:14:18,633
Stay out of this.

262
00:14:18,700 --> 00:14:19,633
You'll get a lot of people hurt.

263
00:14:19,700 --> 00:14:21,133
Stop this!

264
00:14:21,200 --> 00:14:22,300
Why? What about what she did
to you?

265
00:14:22,367 --> 00:14:23,933
Didn't she try to hurt you?

266
00:14:25,733 --> 00:14:27,733
Miss Amanda didn't do anything.

267
00:14:27,800 --> 00:14:29,600
She was just feeling
overwhelmed.

268
00:14:29,700 --> 00:14:30,833
Let's just go home.

269
00:14:30,900 --> 00:14:33,300
Put that away! Come on!

270
00:14:33,367 --> 00:14:34,667
Red, relax.

271
00:14:34,733 --> 00:14:35,933
It's just a toy. See?

272
00:14:37,833 --> 00:14:39,733
You both are crazy!

273
00:14:39,800 --> 00:14:40,800
Stop messing with us!

274
00:14:40,867 --> 00:14:41,967
We'll call the police!

275
00:14:42,033 --> 00:14:43,267
Next time, we won't just mess
with you!

276
00:14:43,333 --> 00:14:44,433
I will bring the real thing!

277
00:14:44,500 --> 00:14:45,667
- Oh, really?
- Mom.

278
00:14:45,733 --> 00:14:48,033
- Mom, stop.
- You see that?

279
00:14:48,100 --> 00:14:49,433
I'll get you, Amanda!

280
00:15:36,567 --> 00:15:37,667
Amanda, time to eat.

281
00:15:39,500 --> 00:15:41,233
Go ahead. I'm not hungry.

282
00:15:45,600 --> 00:15:49,200
Amanda, I'm sorry for keeping
the truth from you.

283
00:15:55,700 --> 00:15:57,567
I was really going to tell you
about it.

284
00:15:57,633 --> 00:16:01,333
You just found out
before I get to tell you.

285
00:16:01,400 --> 00:16:03,067
When I was still in jail,

286
00:16:04,767 --> 00:16:07,867
I often thought of getting out.

287
00:16:09,500 --> 00:16:11,067
Because I wanted to be with you,

288
00:16:12,333 --> 00:16:13,433
especially my daughter.

289
00:16:15,633 --> 00:16:16,933
I always thought...

290
00:16:19,467 --> 00:16:21,967
that I'd finally have peace.

291
00:16:24,600 --> 00:16:26,367
That I'd be happy with Eden.

292
00:16:31,267 --> 00:16:32,933
But why is this happening?

293
00:16:40,267 --> 00:16:41,333
It hurts, Dindi.

294
00:16:45,433 --> 00:16:47,767
I wish I didn't get out of jail

295
00:16:48,867 --> 00:16:51,867
if this is the life
I'll have out here.

296
00:16:51,933 --> 00:16:53,367
No, Amanda!

297
00:16:53,433 --> 00:16:55,133
Eden loves you.

298
00:16:55,200 --> 00:16:57,667
She won't choose anyone
over you!

299
00:17:03,633 --> 00:17:05,033
I don't believe that.

300
00:17:07,567 --> 00:17:09,733
I'm prepared
for what's going to happen.

301
00:17:09,800 --> 00:17:13,367
I know that Eden will choose Red
over me.

302
00:17:16,600 --> 00:17:18,100
I will accept it,

303
00:17:20,467 --> 00:17:21,800
even if it kills me.

304
00:17:34,367 --> 00:17:35,800
Mom, why did you go there?

305
00:17:35,867 --> 00:17:38,267
You and Uncle Zandro could get
in trouble because of that!

306
00:17:38,333 --> 00:17:39,867
Amanda threatened to kill you.

307
00:17:39,933 --> 00:17:41,133
What do you want me to do?
Just sit still?

308
00:17:43,567 --> 00:17:45,233
Where did you hear that from?

309
00:17:45,300 --> 00:17:46,333
Who told you?

310
00:17:46,400 --> 00:17:48,633
It doesn't matter
how I found out.

311
00:17:48,733 --> 00:17:51,467
I can't let Amanda mistreat you!

312
00:17:51,533 --> 00:17:52,533
Look at what happened.

313
00:17:52,600 --> 00:17:53,667
Was I wrong?

314
00:17:53,733 --> 00:17:55,400
She can't do anything about it
now!

315
00:17:56,600 --> 00:17:58,233
What are you two doing?

316
00:17:58,300 --> 00:17:59,900
It's late at night,
and you're still arguing!

317
00:18:01,233 --> 00:18:03,167
This is the only time
I will tell you this!

318
00:18:04,200 --> 00:18:06,433
Stay away from Eden, or else!

319
00:18:06,500 --> 00:18:08,567
Or else what?
You're going to disown me?

320
00:18:08,633 --> 00:18:11,367
- Go ahead!
- Red! Red!

321
00:18:11,433 --> 00:18:13,200
Don't talk to your mom
like that!

322
00:18:14,800 --> 00:18:15,867
She's just concerned about you.

323
00:18:15,933 --> 00:18:16,967
And to our whole family!

324
00:18:17,033 --> 00:18:19,300
What would people think?

325
00:18:19,367 --> 00:18:21,733
That we don't care
about your brother's death?

326
00:18:21,833 --> 00:18:24,633
Why are you thinking
about what people might say?

327
00:18:24,700 --> 00:18:26,233
That's not all!

328
00:18:26,300 --> 00:18:28,733
We're hurt
because of what you are doing,

329
00:18:28,800 --> 00:18:31,533
of your relationship with Eden.

330
00:18:31,600 --> 00:18:33,333
So please, stop!

331
00:18:33,400 --> 00:18:34,267
No!

332
00:18:34,333 --> 00:18:36,533
I love her.
And I will fight for her.

333
00:18:36,600 --> 00:18:39,467
And I don't care what you
or anyone says about it!

334
00:18:39,533 --> 00:18:40,567
- What?
- Victor! Victor!

335
00:18:40,633 --> 00:18:41,900
No, no!

336
00:18:41,967 --> 00:18:43,233
Don't hurt him.

337
00:18:43,300 --> 00:18:45,533
No, he's not our enemy here.

338
00:18:55,267 --> 00:18:59,467
Raichu, I feel awful about this.

339
00:18:59,533 --> 00:19:01,400
Is this what I'll give my mom
in return

340
00:19:01,467 --> 00:19:03,767
after all her sacrifices?

341
00:19:03,833 --> 00:19:05,700
I'm making her cry.

342
00:19:05,767 --> 00:19:06,967
Eden...

343
00:19:07,033 --> 00:19:10,033
She's hurting right now,
but it will pass.

344
00:19:10,100 --> 00:19:14,067
Once she sees how happy you are
with Red, she'll be fine.

345
00:19:14,133 --> 00:19:17,700
And most parents are like that,
anyway. Right?

346
00:19:17,767 --> 00:19:19,233
I don't want to force her

347
00:19:19,300 --> 00:19:20,867
to accept my relationship
with Red.

348
00:19:20,933 --> 00:19:22,800
I don't want to hurt her.

349
00:19:22,867 --> 00:19:24,833
I don't want to make things
worse for her.

350
00:19:26,100 --> 00:19:30,100
Won't you regret letting Red go?

351
00:19:30,200 --> 00:19:35,233
Remember, no parents would want
their kids to suffer.

352
00:19:56,500 --> 00:19:57,700
You're right.

353
00:20:12,400 --> 00:20:13,400
Hello, Red.

354
00:20:14,767 --> 00:20:15,833
Yen.

355
00:20:15,900 --> 00:20:17,367
How are you?

356
00:20:17,433 --> 00:20:19,833
I'm sorry about what happened.

357
00:20:19,900 --> 00:20:23,033
I'm sorry about what my mom did.

358
00:20:23,100 --> 00:20:25,867
But that's not the only reason
I called.

359
00:20:26,967 --> 00:20:28,500
Can I see you tomorrow?

360
00:21:13,200 --> 00:21:14,167
Yen.

361
00:21:16,833 --> 00:21:19,167
I'm sorry,
I just really missed you.

362
00:21:20,533 --> 00:21:21,900
I want you to know that...

363
00:21:23,000 --> 00:21:25,333
I'm not giving up
on our relationship.

364
00:21:26,500 --> 00:21:28,500
No giving up, remember?

365
00:21:28,567 --> 00:21:30,667
I don't care even if my parents
disown me.

366
00:21:31,900 --> 00:21:33,867
Red, don't talk like that.

367
00:21:35,667 --> 00:21:37,300
They're still our parents.

368
00:21:38,867 --> 00:21:41,000
We owe them our life.

369
00:21:41,067 --> 00:21:43,433
That's why we shouldn't hurt
them.

370
00:21:45,700 --> 00:21:49,700
Yen, they want us to break up.

371
00:21:49,767 --> 00:21:53,433
If we do what they want,
we'll end up hurting.

372
00:21:53,500 --> 00:21:54,967
And we both know, that's...

373
00:21:56,067 --> 00:21:57,167
That's unfair to us.

374
00:21:57,233 --> 00:21:58,300
We don't deserve that.

375
00:21:58,367 --> 00:22:01,500
They don't deserve to get hurt,
either.

376
00:22:01,567 --> 00:22:02,767
No one does.

377
00:22:05,167 --> 00:22:09,933
But they have sacrificed a lot
for us.

378
00:22:10,000 --> 00:22:11,533
We should love them.

379
00:22:13,667 --> 00:22:16,400
Can you be happy
while they're hurting?

380
00:22:18,267 --> 00:22:19,533
Because I can't.

381
00:22:23,500 --> 00:22:26,900
My mom has been through a lot.

382
00:22:28,567 --> 00:22:29,967
I can sacrifice everything
for her,

383
00:22:31,567 --> 00:22:33,267
even our relationship.

384
00:22:50,700 --> 00:22:52,567
I heard you when you said
you wanted to meet with him.

385
00:22:52,633 --> 00:22:53,733
Don't try to deny it.

386
00:22:53,800 --> 00:22:57,000
I met with him
to break up with him.

387
00:22:57,067 --> 00:22:58,533
I chose you, Mom.

388
00:22:58,600 --> 00:23:00,567
I don't want to hurt you
anymore.

389
00:23:00,633 --> 00:23:03,467
Are you happy now
that you broke up with Red?

390
00:23:03,533 --> 00:23:04,833
See?

391
00:23:04,900 --> 00:23:07,500
You're not happy.
Beat your record.

392
00:23:07,567 --> 00:23:11,033
If you don't beat your record,
you and Red stay together.

393
00:23:11,100 --> 00:23:13,100
- Eden!
- How are you feeling?

394
00:23:13,167 --> 00:23:14,300
I'm okay.

395
00:23:14,367 --> 00:23:16,367
When was your last menstruation?

396
00:23:16,433 --> 00:23:20,367
You know the right girl
will come at the right time,

397
00:23:20,433 --> 00:23:22,100
from the right family.

398
00:23:22,200 --> 00:23:24,367
Eden is out of the list.

399
00:23:24,433 --> 00:23:27,533
Eden, I hope there won't be
a second line.
